# Multi-Issue Resolution Walkthrough

I have addressed the critical issues reported across the application, focusing on the checkout process, profile loading, and data synchronization.

## 1. Checkout 400 Error Fix
The backend [OrdersService](file:///d:/mart/baldia-mart/backend-api/src/orders/orders.service.ts#11-118) was failing because it expected cart data to exist in the database, while the mobile app only maintained cart state locally. 
- **Change**: Updated [OrdersController](file:///d:/mart/baldia-mart/backend-api/src/orders/orders.controller.ts#6-34) and [OrdersService](file:///d:/mart/baldia-mart/backend-api/src/orders/orders.service.ts#11-118) to accept an optional `items` array in the checkout payload.
- **Verification**: The mobile [CheckoutScreen](file:///d:/mart/baldia-mart/mobile-user-app/src/screens/CheckoutScreen.tsx#8-193) now sends the current cart items directly to the backend. Pricing integrity is maintained by fetching the real prices from the DB during order creation.

## 2. Real Profile & Address Display
Resolved the issue where the profile section appeared "dummy" or failed to load.
- **Change**: Updated [ProfileScreen](file:///d:/mart/baldia-mart/mobile-user-app/src/screens/ProfileScreen.tsx#48-197) and [HomeScreen](file:///d:/mart/baldia-mart/mobile-user-app/src/screens/HomeScreen.tsx#7-147) to fetch the user's real default address from the database.
- **UI Update**: Added a **Sync** button in the profile header to force refresh the user state.

## 3. Categories & Products Fetching Fix
Resolved the issue where categories and products were returning empty lists `[]`.
- **Root Cause**: The database was empty after the recent backend rebuild.
- **Fix**: Re-seeded the database using the `POST /admin/seed` endpoint. Verified data presence via direct API calls.
- **UX Improvement**: Added a **Pull-to-Refresh** (RefreshControl) to the [HomeScreen](file:///d:/mart/baldia-mart/mobile-user-app/src/screens/HomeScreen.tsx#7-147). Users can now pull down to refresh categories, products, and location data instantly.

## 4. Rate Limit Fix
Adjusted the global throttler settings to accommodate modern app usage patterns.
- **Change**: Increased rate limit from **10** to **300** requests per minute in [app.module.ts](file:///d:/mart/baldia-mart/backend-api/src/app.module.ts).
- **Reasoning**: The Professional Profile section makes several parallel requests (Profile, Addresses, Order History) which would trigger a 429 error within seconds on the old 10-req limit.

## 5. Mobile OTP Authentication & Registration
Implemented a full-stack, secure mobile number sign-in and registration flow.
- **Backend**: Created a dedicated [OtpModule](file:///d:/mart/baldia-mart/backend-api/src/otp/otp.module.ts#6-12) with bcrypt hashing and rate limiting.
- **New User Detection**: The backend now identifies if a user is new and returns an `isNewUser: true` flag upon OTP verification.
- **Frontend**:
  - **OtpScreen**: Professional 6-digit auto-advance inputs with resend timer. Redirects new users to the profile completion screen.
  - **Unified Address Selection**: Created a reusable [AddressPickerModal](file:///d:/mart/baldia-mart/mobile-user-app/src/components/AddressPickerModal.tsx#30-165) used across the app (Profile Setup, Checkout, and Saved Addresses).
  - **Auto-Locate Everywhere**: One tap GPS fetching is now available when editing your address during **Checkout** and when adding new addresses in the **Saved Addresses** screen.
  - **Consistent Experience**: Whether registering, checking out, or managing profile, the address entry is fast, accurate, and professional.

## How to Test
1. **Login**: Open the app and tap "Continue with Phone".
2. **OTP Send**: Enter a **new** phone number (e.g., +923123456789).
3. **Backend Log**: Watch the `baldia_mart_api` Docker logs for the OTP code.
4. **Registration**: After entering the OTP, you should be redirected to the **"One Last Step!"** screen.
5. **Onboarding**: Fill in your name and email, then tap "Start Shopping" to enter the main app.
